,Not Recommended,238870,9576845,"Posted: 20 March, 2014",all,Stuball3d,"I bought this game on a whim, since it was only $10 at the time. I was expecting a clone of the Stronghold series, with perhaps some embelishments or improvements. This game provides neither. In fact, it can't even provide the basic expectations of an RTS game. After playing it for about an hour I was surprised to see this wasn't an 'Early Access' game, but instead claims to be 'complete.'  The game most lacks in its user interface (UI), which if improved, would bring it at least on par to other RTSes.Areas for improvement:1. Double-clicking a control group (0-9) doesn't center on units. And there is no additional key to do so. This is unforgivable.2. The game helpfully informs you that you are under attack. Hope you noticed that one minimap ping, because otherwise you're clicking through controls groups trying to find the one taking damage, and then remembering where that group is (see 1 above). There needs to be a 'zoom to last alert' key or equivalent.3. Speaking of minimap. When you have a unit selected, the unit info covers half of the minimap. You can hide the minimap, and the unit info. But maybe they should just make the unit info smaller... Or make the minimap movable?4. Trees block building. And I didn't find a way to manually dfestroy a tree. I looked in the keybinds, and found what can be best called a 'minimalist' interface. You have WASD camera controls (not my cup of tea for an RTS, but whatever), control groups (0-9), and then a couple keys for peasant (resource gatherer) management. No attack-move, manual attack, zoom-to-unit, etc.This game might have potential, if like I said, it was not billed as complete. There's much more I would want, but those listed I think are some bare-minimums needed to make it playable.  To be honest, I haven't played long, but I found myself fighting the game controls and 'lost' for most of it. Pick up Stronghold to fill your midievil RTS needs."
