76561197976537479,Not Recommended,238870,9612218,"Posted: 23 March, 2014",all,Tofu_Cannibal,"I do not usually write reviews, but I felt the need to warn people about this game. This is a fun concept if you enjoy strategy games or like whole castle/fortess theme. The problem is the game is designed as though the last 10 years of game developement never happened. There are no tool tips for the majority of the interfaces. You are left to guess what upgrades actually do. There are three game types in skirmish mode, but you are not told any of the information until you launch them. The settings section has you clicking through options one at a time instead of having a drop down menu. The game has a 99 population limit, which would make sense if it was a game with a lot of micro managing of individual units - it is not. Most of the challenge in the game is figuring out how to deal with the tiny population limits and figuring out how to get a wall that is glitched built before the next attack.Essentially if this game came out in 2004 it would have been amazing, but it plays like a game from then with some updated graphics and plenty of bugs with walls and structures. I do not recommend it. I feel sorry for the people that worked really hard on this, because it just didn't come together."
